  "name": "Deity's Strike",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>A manifested version of your deity's favored weapon appears in the air above and attacks the target, using your spell attack roll. On a hit, the weapon deals 7d12 force damage, or double damage on a critical hit.</p>\n<p>After the attack, whether it succeeds or fails, divine energy bursts from the weapon in a shock wave. It emits in a <strong>10-foot-wide, 30-foot-long line</strong> starting from the target and continuing in a direction you choose. Choose an alignment your deity has (chaotic, evil, good, or lawful). Your target and any other creatures within the area of the spell take [[/r 5d6]] damage of the chosen alignment type, with a basic Reflex save. The spell gains the trait of the alignment you choose. If your deity is true neutral, the weapon doesn't create a shock wave.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (9th)</strong> The force damage increases by 1d12 and the alignment damage increases by 1d6. ([[/r 6d6]])</p>"
